01:14.600 --> 01:17.900
precisely because they are so different in character.

01:17.900 --> 01:22.100
Jesper describes planarchy as, and I quote here,

01:22.100 --> 01:32.000
an organization of human activity that accepts the fundamentally self-directed, spontaneous and creative character of human action, end quote.

01:32.000 --> 01:38.300
And while he correctly points out that this is fundamentally incompatible with central planning,

01:38.300 --> 01:51.000
I think that the bottom-up type of approach that Daniel E. Serow's puts forward has at least some elements in it that can be fruitfully merged with an idea of planarchy,

01:51.000 --> 01:53.400
as Jesper describes it.

