48:19.400 --> 48:29.400
Well, I asked him, I asked Saros in the interview, and I mean, it depends on what, which kind of face we're talking about, of course, because that's the essential differentiation.

48:29.400 --> 48:44.400
So in the in the in the first phase, then it would be it would have to have some kind of size in terms of production in order to be eligible to to receive what you kind of can see as a base income, you know.

48:44.400 --> 48:50.400
